AIM
To simulate DES encryption of a 64-bit block using basic XOR operations (NOT full DES).
def des_simple_encrypt(block, key):
    return "".join("1" if block[i] != key[i] else "0" for i in range(64))

plaintext = "01010101" * 8      # 64 bits
key =       "11110000" * 8      # 64 bits

cipher = des_simple_encrypt(plaintext, key)

print("Plaintext:", plaintext)
print("Key:", key)
print("Ciphertext:", cipher)
Result

Simple DES-like XOR encryption is demonstrated on a 64-bit block.
